# Internal / planning docs (kept locally, not for contributors). The WHOLE directory, no exceptions:
# event-schema.md was briefly tracked as the songcore spec, but it is internal design material and
# doesn't belong in a public repo. Its §9 rule (a schema change lands with the code + regenerated
# goldens in one commit) still holds — the schema is enforced in-repo by songcore/event.h, the
# conformance goldens in /testdata, and the tools that compare against them.
#
# The trailing slash matters, and so does the leading one: `/docs/internal/` ignores the DIRECTORY, so
# git never descends into it and no later negation pattern can accidentally re-include a file from it.
# The old `docs/internal/*` only ignored the entries, one by one.
/docs/internal/

# APK artifacts — release APKs go to GitHub Releases, not the repo
apk/

# Device-recorded conformance traces — scratch input for the GoldenTraceTest cross-check,
# never committed (the committed truth is /testdata/traces)
/testdata/device/

# Keep build helper scripts (don't ignore)
!build.sh
!test.sh
!clean.sh

# Gradle wrapper JAR must be committed — it bootstraps the build on CI and fresh clones
!gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar
